# Entities Style

- Use Lombok for entity boilerplate (`@Data`, constructors, `@Builder`) to keep classes compact.
- Define table and column mapping directly on fields with explicit `@Table`/`@Column` metadata.
- Use `@GeneratedValue(strategy = GenerationType.SEQUENCE)` for primary keys.
- Model collection relationships as `Set<>` with `@Builder.Default` and eager initialization.
- Keep join table names explicit (`user_roles`, `user_owned_items`, etc.) with `@JoinTable`.
- Preserve practical domain helper methods on model objects when useful (`toString()`, derived view data).
- Keep entity field names aligned with DTO names to support simple mapper-based conversion.
